      "updated": 1779717426904,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "3. Content Delivery Networks (CDN)\n\nA Content Delivery Network (CDN) is a globally distributed network of servers that speeds up web content \nlike images, videos, static pages(html) etc. ,delivery by caching copies of files on edge servers located \ncloser to users than the central origin server. ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "3. Content Delivery Networks (CDN)\n\nA Content Delivery Network (CDN) is a globally distributed network of servers that speeds up web content \nlike images, videos, static pages(html) etc. ,delivery by caching copies of files on edge servers located \ncloser to users than the central origin server. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
